WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.267 --> 00:00:03.370
Never, Never go creeks!

00:00:03.970 --> 00:00:06.039
This case, like so many others,

00:00:06.272 --> 00:00:09.075
highlights two critical mistakes that hikers often make,

00:00:09.376 --> 00:00:11.711
especially in mountains like Taiwan's.

00:00:12.645 --> 00:00:17.317
First, never underestimate the mountains by relying on your 'good navigation sense'

00:00:17.484 --> 00:00:19.285
and neglecting GPS technology.

00:00:19.819 --> 00:00:22.789
Always carry one GPS device with offline maps,

00:00:22.956 --> 00:00:24.424
and know how to use it.

00:00:25.358 --> 00:00:29.662
For advanced hikers, I even suggest carrying two GPS devices—for instance,

00:00:29.929 --> 00:00:33.900
a GPS watch that's waterproof and has much longer battery life.

00:00:36.102 --> 00:00:39.372
Second, if you're truly unable to find your original trail,

00:00:39.606 --> 00:00:42.075
never descend down in unknown terrain.

00:00:42.609 --> 00:00:45.412
Your best chance is to stay put, conserve energy,

00:00:45.645 --> 00:00:47.614
focus on temperature management overnight,

00:00:47.947 --> 00:00:50.016
and wait for organized search and rescue,

00:00:50.150 --> 00:00:54.521
especially if you've shared your location and announced you need help.

00:00:54.687 --> 00:00:56.689
Your chances dramatically improve.

